pageContext.claim: “The last administration was Sleepy Joe and Obama tried to ram through one of the worst trade deals ever negotiated, worse than NAFTA, worse than WTO. It was called the Trans-Pacific Partnership. It would have been a disaster.”
pageContext.analysis: This doomsday prediction is belied by the fact that many of the digital trade and labor provisions in Trump's proposed USMCA trade agreement with Canada and Mexico are lifted from the Trans-Pacific Partnership, which Trump killed early in his term.
